As Snogpitch said, it was available on GEnie.  I got it in the distribution
archive for EBBS 128.  There was also a C64 version that was distributed with
EBBS 64.  Below is a brief description.

Goofed.128 runs on a C128 in either 80 or 40 column mode.  It was released
by Ed Parry as freeware in 1990.  Documentation is internal.

Goofed is a line based text editor.  It has built-in directory and DOS wedge
functions.  Word-wrap is automatic and adjustable from 20 to 254 columns.

I can send it as an email attachment.  If you, or anyone else, would like a
copy, either leave a message here, or de-spam my email address and send an
email request.  It is about 19 Kb in size.
